    <name>
				<text>37.2.3.6 A terminal that requires attention</text>
		</name>
    <questiontext format="moodle_auto_format">
				<text><![CDATA[<p class="HELM_exercise">Exercise</p><p>A computer installation has {@n@} terminals. Independently, the probability that any one terminal
will require attention during a week is {@p@}. Find the probabilities that</p><ol class="HELM_parts">

<li><p>0 terminals will require attention during the next week: [[input:ans1]] [[validation:ans1]] [[feedback:prt1]]</p></li>

<li><p>1 terminal will require attention during the next week: [[input:ans2]] [[validation:ans2]] [[feedback:prt2]]</p></li>

<li><p>2 terminals will require attention during the next week: [[input:ans3]] [[validation:ans3]] [[feedback:prt3]]</p></li>

<li><p>3 or more terminals will require attention during the next week: [[input:ans4]] [[validation:ans4]] [[feedback:prt4]]</p></li>

</ol><p><b>Note:</b> please round your answer to \(4\) decimal places.</p>]]></text>
		</questiontext>
    <generalfeedback format="moodle_auto_format">
				<text><![CDATA[<p><b>SOLUTION:</b></p><p>As we suspect, this experiment follows a Binomial distribution&nbsp;\(\text{P} (X=r)=\&nbsp; ^n\!C_rp^r(1-p)^{n-r}\) where \(p\) is the probability that any one terminal will require attention during a week</p>
<ol class="HELM_parts">
  <li>\(\text{P} (X=0)=\  ^{{@n@}}\!C_0({@p@})^0(1-{@p@})^{@n@}=({@1-p@})^{@n@}={@ta_1@}\)</li>
  <li><p><span class="math display">\(\text{P} (X=1) =\&nbsp;^{{@n@}}\!C_1({@p@})^1(1-{@p@})^{@n-1@} = {@ta_2@}\)</span></p></li>
 <li><p><span class="math display">\( \text{P} (X=2) =\&nbsp;^{{@n@}}\!C_2({@p@})^2(1-{@p@})^{@n-2@} = {@ta_3@}\)</span></p></li>
  <li>\( \text{P} (X\ge 3)= 1 - \text{P}(X=0) - \text{P}(X=1) -&nbsp;\text{P}(X=2) =&nbsp;{@ta_4@}\)</li></ol>]]></text>
		</generalfeedback>
